    Rarities are based on the list compiled by Paul Nurnbegrer.  The letter
    indicates the 121 card print sheet on which the card appears (Common,
    Uncommon and Rare) and the number indicates the number of appearances on
    the sheet.  Thus a U2 card is a card that appears twice per Uncommon
    sheet and, thus, makes up 2 of the 121 Uncommon cards per sheet.  Sample
    cards (rarity S) were available at GenCon and from SCRYE magazine and
    are all of equal rarity.  Numbers listed with the S cards are their card
    number in the regular series.  Not all S cards appear in the regular
    series, however.

